text: Sompeta Assembly constituency was a constituency of the Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly, India until 2008 in Srikakulam district. ==Overview== It was a part of the Srikakulam Lok Sabha constituency along with another six Vidhan Sabha segments, namely, Palasa, Tekkali, Pathapatnam, Srikakulam, Amadalavalasa and Narasannapeta. ==Members of Legislative Assembly== * 1951:Gouthu Latchanna * 1955:Gouthu Latchanna * 1962: Gouthu Latchanna * 1967: Gouthu Latchanna * 1972: Majji Thulasi Das * 1978: Gouthu Latchanna * 1983: Majji Narayana Rao, Indian National Congress * 1985: Gouthu Syam Sunder Sivaji, Telugu Desam Party * 1989: Gouthu Syam Sunder Sivaji, Telugu Desam Party * 1994: Gouthu Syam Sunder Sivaji Telugu Desam Party * 1999: Gouthu Syam Sunder Sivaji, Telugu Desam Party * 2004: Gouthu Syam Sunder Sivaji Telugu Desam Party ==See also== * List of constituencies of Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly Category:Assembly constituencies of Srikakulam district Category:Assembly constituencies of Andhra Pradesh Category:Politics of Andhra Pradesh
title: Sompeta (Assembly constituency)
